data.product_description: The MacBook Pro "Core i5" 1.4 13-Inch (2019, Touch Bar, Two Thunderbolt 3 Ports) is powered by a 14 nm, 8th Generation "Coffee Lake" 1.4 GHz Intel "Core i5" processor (I5-8257U), with four independent processor "cores" on a single silicon chip, 128 MB of eDRAM embedded on the processor die, and a shared 6 MB level 3 cache. This notebook also packs 8 GB of onboard 2133 MHz LPDDR3 SDRAM, 256 GB of flash storage, and an integrated Intel Iris Plus Graphics 645 graphics processor that shares memory with the system. Additionally, it has a high-resolution LED-backlit 13.3" widescreen 2560x1600 (227 ppi, 500 nits) "Retina" display with True Tone technology, and a integrated battery that provides an Apple estimated 10 hours of runtime.
